article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 68, Cal Poly-SLO 54
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Gerard Anderson scored 20 points and Jer'Vaughn Johnson added 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead Cal State-Fullerton to a 68-54 victory against Cal Poly on Thursday night. Bryce Webster and Devon Peltier had 11 points each for Fullerton (8-7, 3-1 Big West), which moved into first in the conference standings. Lorenzo Keeler scored 13 points and Shawn Lewis 12 for Cal Poly (5-10, 2-2). A 13-4 run by Cal Poly cut Fullerton's lead to 57-52 with 2:07 remaining. But the Mustangs missed their last four field-goal tries and turned the ball over on two other possessions, enabling the Titans to ice the game from the free-throw line. Cal Poly shot just 33 percent (15 of 45) from the floor. Fullerton shot 37 percent but made 30 of 37 free-throw attempts.
